00:22:48,034 --> 00:22:50,453
Them Greeks and those twisted-ass names.

244
00:22:50,537 --> 00:22:52,872
The Greeks invented civilization.

245
00:22:52,956 --> 00:22:54,332
Yeah? Ass-fucking, too.

246
00:22:54,415 --> 00:22:57,210
What exactly do we know
about vondopoulos?

247
00:22:57,293 --> 00:23:00,547
We should stay on
him, see who he really is.

248
00:23:00,630 --> 00:23:02,215
How about it?

249
00:23:02,298 --> 00:23:05,260
Throw us a few
of your well-equipped surveillance teams?

250
00:23:06,177 --> 00:23:09,055
In case you haven't noticed,
I'm the only fed still in the room.

251
00:23:09,138 --> 00:23:12,392
The us attorney has what he wants
with the union guys

252
00:23:12,475 --> 00:23:16,104
which means my field office
is pretty much over this case.

253
00:23:16,187 --> 00:23:19,065
Ok, we're on vondopoulos ourselves.

254
00:23:23,486 --> 00:23:27,448
I'm sorry for him. And for you.

255
00:23:29,617 --> 00:23:32,745
We should've paid
more attention to our own.

256
00:23:32,829 --> 00:23:36,165
Like I could've stopped Ziggy
from what he done.

257
00:23:36,583 --> 00:23:38,626
Like anyone could ever control him.

258
00:23:38,710 --> 00:23:41,170
I was thinking of my boy, too.

259
00:23:43,715 --> 00:23:46,009
They're dropping the net on all the guys.

260
00:23:46,092 --> 00:23:49,679
Ain't no secret things get lost
in them cans. He'll be all right.

261
00:23:51,180 --> 00:23:53,516
They tossed my house, frank.

262
00:23:54,017 --> 00:23:57,979
They don't do that when there's
a couple of cases of vodka missing.

263
00:23:59,731 --> 00:24:04,652
They made me sign the search warrant.
That's a receipt, like, for what they found.

264
00:24:05,653 --> 00:24:08,615
Heroin, frank. From this house.

265
00:24:09,324 --> 00:24:12,827
No, that ain't right. That can't be right.

266
00:24:13,870 --> 00:24:18,374
I knew Nicky and zig was boosting stuff.
Cameras, shit like that. Nothing like this.

267
00:24:18,458 --> 00:24:19,709
You knew?

268
00:24:21,461 --> 00:24:24,797
And once Nicky got used to boosting stuff
and seeing money,

269
00:24:24,881 --> 00:24:26,191
what did you think he was gonna do?

270
00:24:26,215 --> 00:24:28,718
Turn straight all of a
sudden and give it up?

271
00:24:29,552 --> 00:24:30,762
No, frank.

272
00:24:31,721 --> 00:24:35,016
Once you gave him
a taste on the house, just...

273
00:24:35,099 --> 00:24:40,021
That was never... I mean, he knew. He knew.

274
00:24:40,104 --> 00:24:41,814
Everything I did, the cans I let through,

275
00:24:41,898 --> 00:24:44,817
the money we got
went to keeping what we had.

276
00:24:44,901 --> 00:24:46,736
God damn it, frank!

277
00:24:48,404 --> 00:24:52,492
Don't let that excuse this. Not this.

278
00:24:55,620 --> 00:24:58,790
Uncle frank, with the big shoulders.

279
00:24:58,873 --> 00:25:03,711
"If it's broke, give it to my uncle.
He can fix it."

280
00:25:22,271 --> 00:25:26,776
I'm going uptown if this
motherfucker gonna close at midnight.

281
00:25:29,153 --> 00:25:32,240
Hey, killer.
I got something for you, come here.

282
00:25:48,297 --> 00:25:50,299
You got the new Harper's yet?

283
00:25:52,343 --> 00:25:53,720
Now, you know stores down the way

284
00:25:53,803 --> 00:25:57,223
don't have nothing past vibes
and handguns today.

285
00:25:57,306 --> 00:25:59,767
Some titty mags, too, if you need.

286
00:25:59,851 --> 00:26:02,186
All right. I got you.

287
00:26:02,270 --> 00:26:05,440
I'm gonna hook you up, though, all right?

288
00:26:09,652 --> 00:26:12,780
Hey, boy. Told you I had something for you.

289
00:26:12,864 --> 00:26:14,490
There you go.

290
00:26:15,366 --> 00:26:16,784
That's my good boy.

291
00:27:07,794 --> 00:27:09,337
Good day for a ship.

292
00:27:10,129 --> 00:27:13,841
This is the hiring hall, frank.
Working stevedores only.

293
00:27:17,887 --> 00:27:19,597
Big Roy, let me have your card.

294
00:27:22,266 --> 00:27:23,601
What do you want it for?

295
00:27:23,684 --> 00:27:26,312
Not you. Little big Roy,
let me hold your card.

296
00:27:26,938 --> 00:27:29,482
Ineedit
I'm gonna work the cape St. George today.

297
00:27:29,565 --> 00:27:32,151
- I'll work it for you.
- Work it for me?

298
00:27:32,235 --> 00:27:37,782
I work the ship. You work a barstool down
clement street. End of the week, you get paid.

299
00:27:53,631 --> 00:27:55,591
Hey, Phil.

300
00:27:56,926 --> 00:27:58,928
I'm putting up for the cape St. George.

301
00:27:59,679 --> 00:28:01,556
I don't see no resemblance.

302
00:28:01,639 --> 00:28:05,560
We're both bald, we're both polacks.
What the fuck else you need to know?

303
00:28:26,747 --> 00:28:28,624
Who's gonna work for me?

304
00:28:30,668 --> 00:28:34,755
- A different look for our boy.
- Perry Ellis or something.

305
00:28:34,839 --> 00:28:40,928
How would a just-rolled-out-of-bed-looking
motherfucker like you know the designer?

306
00:28:42,305 --> 00:28:44,307
Ok, I'm guessing.

307
00:28:45,808 --> 00:28:48,102
It's a Joseph abboud.

308
00:28:48,185 --> 00:28:52,982
He puts dark buttons instead of brass on
his blazers. That's the abboud signature.

309
00:28:53,065 --> 00:28:56,611
You know what they call a guy who pays
that much attention to his clothes?

310
00:28:56,694 --> 00:28:59,697
Mm-hm. A grown-up.

311
00:29:01,574 --> 00:29:03,200
We're up.

312
00:29:04,118 --> 00:29:07,413
- 12-14, let's go.
- Copy, 11-34.

313
00:29:23,346 --> 00:29:25,723
- That's a first.
- Sweat from a checker.

314
00:30:00,091 --> 00:30:01,884
- You all right?
- Ready.

315
00:30:04,178 --> 00:30:06,639
Maybe you should set up an easel
on the sidewalk

316
00:30:06,722 --> 00:30:09,350
- and do a sketch instead.
- I'm fine.

317
00:30:09,433 --> 00:30:11,060
Mm-hm.

318
00:30:34,875 --> 00:30:39,130
- Anything I ought to know?
- Yeah. Use the city.

319
00:30:39,213 --> 00:30:43,134
Windows, mirrors, reflections,
anything like that.

320
00:30:46,429 --> 00:30:48,639
Stay on my frequency, hear?

321
00:30:52,143 --> 00:30:56,063
Vondopoulos should be coming out on foot
right about now.

322
00:30:56,147 --> 00:30:57,565
Copy that.

323
00:31:59,835 --> 00:32:02,588
Beadie Russell.
She wasn't much when we started, you know.

324
00:32:03,297 --> 00:32:06,133
- But now she's got game.
- Mm-hm.

325
00:32:28,364 --> 00:32:29,657
Thank you.

326
00:33:23,419 --> 00:33:26,964
12-14. I got him going
into a fifth-floor room.

327
00:33:27,047 --> 00:33:29,383
Note the number
then get down to the lobby.

328
00:33:29,466 --> 00:33:32,428
- Wait on him there.
- Copy.

329
00:33:47,067 --> 00:33:50,988
She's got vondopoulos in a room.
It could be a while.

330
00:33:51,071 --> 00:33:52,448
Copy.

331
00:34:03,667 --> 00:34:06,670
- All this shit's going on to chassis?
- So they tell me.

332
00:34:06,754 --> 00:34:09,715
We need a fork-lift.
We're almost done here.

333
00:34:25,481 --> 00:34:28,901
12-14. Vondopoulos and another
man, middle-aged, blue suit,

334
00:34:28,984 --> 00:34:30,424
leaving the front door of the hotel.

335
00:34:30,486 --> 00:34:32,112
They're just behind me. Copy?

336
00:34:32,780 --> 00:34:33,906
Copy.

337
00:34:35,366 --> 00:34:36,533
11-34.

338
00:34:36,742 --> 00:34:40,579
Subject and companion, blue suit,
leaving the hotel any moment now.

339
00:34:40,663 --> 00:34:42,665
Copy, we got the eyeball.

340
00:34:50,339 --> 00:34:52,299
The man with vondopoulos must be big.

341
00:34:53,634 --> 00:34:57,554
- I mean, look at that expensive suit.
- Yeah, with them buttons and all.

342
00:35:15,864 --> 00:35:17,408
We leave the benz here?

343
00:35:17,491 --> 00:35:20,452
It's hot.

344
00:35:37,219 --> 00:35:39,638
They didn't come back to the benz. Got 'em?

345
00:35:39,722 --> 00:35:41,557
Negative.

346
00:36:34,276 --> 00:36:37,237
- You about done?
- These nine here still got to be stripped.

347
00:36:37,321 --> 00:36:39,656
- Harder than it looks.
- What ain't?

348
00:36:39,740 --> 00:36:41,241
Frank?

349
00:36:42,326 --> 00:36:46,163
- You hear how moonshot got his name?
- Yeah, and I could give a fuck.

350
00:36:48,290 --> 00:36:50,334
Who was the room registered to?

351
00:36:50,417 --> 00:36:54,963
Er... Steven rados.
He gave a northwest DC address.

352
00:36:55,047 --> 00:36:57,841
Maybe that's the man with the good tailor.
Maybe not.

353
00:36:58,467 --> 00:37:01,512
We should run out the paper trail
on this guy, see what we turn up.

354
00:37:03,138 --> 00:37:06,058
As to our only tangible piece of progress
from the raids,

355
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:09,353
what can we do for our friend white Mike?

356
00:37:09,436 --> 00:37:12,398
He rolls on his suppliers,
and he can walk with a long probation.

357
00:37:13,273 --> 00:37:17,277
- And we can move him if he needs.
- Witness protection?

358
00:37:17,361 --> 00:37:20,781
Why have the feds with you if they're
not gonna step up every now and then?

359
00:37:22,032 --> 00:37:25,411
Wait a second. You're gonna give
a drug dealer a ride like that?

360
00:37:25,494 --> 00:37:29,665
- What about frank sobotka?
- Feds took a shot at him and got nothing.

361
00:37:29,748 --> 00:37:31,208
Or so they tell me.

362
00:37:31,291 --> 00:37:33,752
They cared more about busting the union...

363
00:37:33,836 --> 00:37:38,257
Than anything else in the case.
If we came at frank straight?

364
00:37:39,383 --> 00:37:42,177
You can't make him
any kind of specific offer yourself.

365
00:37:42,261 --> 00:37:45,556
Only I can do that, and only after
I get an ok from my front office.

366
00:37:45,639 --> 00:37:49,685
- She could plant the seed.
- There's no better messenger, counselor.

367
00:37:52,104 --> 00:37:53,188
Take a shot.

368
00:37:54,440 --> 00:37:58,444
- You going to his house?
- The union hall. That's his house.

369
00:38:00,195 --> 00:38:02,489
Thanks for waiting, brucie. Sorry I'm late.

370
00:38:02,573 --> 00:38:04,324
I shouldn't even be seen with you.

371
00:38:04,408 --> 00:38:06,285
I wanna settle our business while we can.

372
00:38:06,368 --> 00:38:09,955
It ain't like I'm gonna get my hands
on more cash, obviously.

373
00:38:10,038 --> 00:38:11,707
The grain pier is dead.

374
00:38:13,459 --> 00:38:18,297
Half the votes we had lined up are walking
sideways now. They read the paper, frank.

375
00:38:18,714 --> 00:38:22,968
So what? So I'm dirty. The grain
pier's still the grain pier, right?

376
00:38:23,051 --> 00:38:25,095
They ain't voting for
me! It ain't about me!

377
00:38:25,179 --> 00:38:30,142
I'm not gonna lie. No one is gonna
stand with us now that the FBI is on you.

378
00:38:30,225 --> 00:38:32,811
- They're scared.
- Of what?

379
00:38:32,895 --> 00:38:34,480
They took the money.

380
00:38:34,563 --> 00:38:38,484
And now if they deliver the votes,
they figure the feds will be on them, too.

381
00:38:38,567 --> 00:38:39,776
I'm sorry, frank.

382
00:38:40,944 --> 00:38:45,866
You find a way to put this FBI thing to bed,
maybe we can come back with the grain pier.

383
00:38:45,949 --> 00:38:50,704
You'll have a couple of people down there
knowing they owe you a vote or two.

384
00:38:51,872 --> 00:38:55,626
I don't know what else to say.
I don't. I'm sorry, frank.

385
00:38:59,046 --> 00:39:01,757
You know what the trouble is, brucie?

386
00:39:05,010 --> 00:39:08,305
We used to make shit in this country.
Build shit.

387
00:39:10,265 --> 00:39:13,435
Now we just put our hand
in the next guy's pocket.

388
00:39:34,289 --> 00:39:38,835
Come on, you can't eat only olives.
Order something. Lamb or something.

389
00:39:38,919 --> 00:39:40,462
I'm not hungry.

390
00:39:45,133 --> 00:39:48,971
All this trouble.

391
00:39:50,472 --> 00:39:54,351
- So, our associates, they are strong?
- Yes.

392
00:39:54,434 --> 00:39:58,105
I don't worry about our people.
We can try to get them out before trial.

393
00:39:58,188 --> 00:40:00,899
If not, they will stand for us.

394
00:40:00,983 --> 00:40:05,070
We have shown them too much.
There will be no more trouble.

395
00:40:06,071 --> 00:40:08,657
We must make certain of this.

396
00:40:08,991 --> 00:40:12,619
- Maybe there's another way.
- There is only one sure way.

397
00:40:12,828 --> 00:40:13,912
Hear me out.

398
00:40:13,996 --> 00:40:19,001
If I could guarantee that frank sobotka
and his nephew would be silent,

399
00:40:20,294 --> 00:40:22,170
wouldn't you prefer that?

400
00:40:22,921 --> 00:40:24,756
But you cannot guarantee this.

401
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:28,385
Frank's son,
the idiot who shot George in his store.

402
00:40:29,261 --> 00:40:32,514
He's going to jail for a long time

403
00:40:32,598 --> 00:40:33,849
unless...

404
00:40:36,852 --> 00:40:40,355
There was a young clerk wounded that day
in the store.

405
00:40:41,106 --> 00:40:45,652
The prosecutors want to use
him as a witness. I know his family.

406
00:40:47,195 --> 00:40:50,115
Frank sobotka will have his son back.

407
00:40:50,198 --> 00:40:53,702
If a man can have this,
why would he talk to the police?

408
00:40:54,202 --> 00:40:56,246
What about frank's nephew?

409
00:40:56,330 --> 00:40:59,249
He is the idiot's cousin.
He wants the same thing as frank.

410
00:40:59,333 --> 00:41:05,422
Anyway, I don't worry about Niko.

411
00:41:06,089 --> 00:41:08,133
You are fond of him, spiros.

412
00:41:09,092 --> 00:41:11,011
You should have had a son.

413
00:41:11,553 --> 00:41:14,473
But then I would have had a wife.

414
00:41:24,900 --> 00:41:28,945
If this maggot doesn't post by midnight,
I'm gonna take it personal.

415
00:41:32,866 --> 00:41:35,619
The shitbird lives at
his parents' basement.

416
00:41:38,622 --> 00:41:41,166
Where's a guy like that gonna run?

417
00:42:21,123 --> 00:42:23,750
You wanna go with auntie tosha? Come on.

418
00:42:26,336 --> 00:42:27,796
Nice and easy, honey.

419
00:42:27,879 --> 00:42:30,841
- Come on. Come here.
- All right. Come on, baby.

420
00:42:30,924 --> 00:42:33,927
What's up, big man? Where the party at?

421
00:42:34,010 --> 00:42:35,846
Ain't no party up in here, girl.

422
00:42:35,929 --> 00:42:42,519
We thought Darnell and everybody was gonna
get their smoke on. Ain't you know Darnell?

423
00:42:42,602 --> 00:42:44,646
What's this good boy's name?

424
00:42:45,105 --> 00:42:46,231
Hey, boy.

425
00:42:47,107 --> 00:42:48,567
How you doing today?

426
00:42:48,650 --> 00:42:50,527
You been good? This a good boy.

427
00:42:51,987 --> 00:42:54,865
- There it is.
- Car will be running.

428
00:43:00,370 --> 00:43:01,663
What is it, Lamar?

429
00:43:10,130 --> 00:43:12,257
No need to prolong this.

430
00:43:12,966 --> 00:43:14,843
No, we got time.

431
00:43:14,926 --> 00:43:18,096
- You kill my man?
- No, he restin'.

432
00:43:21,516 --> 00:43:25,771
- I'm saying, ain't you wanna know?
- Not particularly.

433
00:43:26,855 --> 00:43:29,900
About a year ago, a boy name Brandon
got got here in Baltimore.

434
00:43:29,983 --> 00:43:32,194
Stuck and burned before he passed.

435
00:43:33,111 --> 00:43:36,698
- The game is the game.
- Indeed.

436
00:43:37,199 --> 00:43:38,992
But see, that boy was beautiful.

437
00:43:39,534 --> 00:43:43,371
Wasn't no need for y'all to do him
the way y'all did. You feel me?

438
00:43:43,455 --> 00:43:45,999
- A year, you say?
- About that.

439
00:43:48,877 --> 00:43:51,463
You've got some wrong information.

440
00:43:51,546 --> 00:43:53,298
Man, you lying to live.

441
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:56,593
I'm at peace with my god.

442
00:43:57,844 --> 00:43:59,387
Do what you will.

443
00:44:17,531 --> 00:44:18,865
So you know?

444
00:44:19,866 --> 00:44:23,286
What happened to your
boy, it's not my style.

445
00:44:29,417 --> 00:44:33,547
The way you bleeding out your back,
looks like that bullet bore clean through.

446
00:44:35,423 --> 00:44:37,759
Nine at close range will do that.

447
00:44:48,061 --> 00:44:50,522
Emergency. Police or ambulance?

448
00:44:50,605 --> 00:44:53,358
I wanna report a shooting at the new motel.

449
00:44:53,441 --> 00:44:56,820
- On north Avenue. Room 221.
- Sir?

450
00:45:30,478 --> 00:45:32,147
My pal, Beatrice.

451
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:37,152
What, you gonna run me in again?
Isn't that like double jeopardy?

452
00:45:37,235 --> 00:45:39,237
Stop it, just stop it.

453
00:45:42,198 --> 00:45:44,743
- Talk to me.
- And say what?

454
00:45:49,956 --> 00:45:52,542
I'm sitting here trying
to figure it out myself.

455
00:45:52,626 --> 00:45:54,711
It didn't happen overnight.

456
00:46:05,013 --> 00:46:06,848
I knew I was wrong.

457
00:46:08,683 --> 00:46:10,977
But I thought I was wrong
for the right reasons.

458
00:46:11,811 --> 00:46:14,147
There are different kinds of wrong.

459
00:46:18,068 --> 00:46:19,653
What're you doing here, bea?

460
00:46:22,030 --> 00:46:25,450
I'd like you to come in. Not in cuffs.

461
00:46:26,868 --> 00:46:28,870
Because you want to.

462
00:46:30,330 --> 00:46:32,540
I'm opening a door here, frank.

463
00:46:41,967 --> 00:46:44,302
I can't promise you anything.

464
00:46:45,845 --> 00:46:48,682
Just come in. We'll start from there.

465
00:46:54,312 --> 00:46:57,273
You're better than
them you got in bed with.

466
00:47:07,158 --> 00:47:10,704
Our man vondopoulos didn't come home?
Maybe he got lucky.

467
00:47:14,249 --> 00:47:15,750
Maybe we didn't.

468
00:47:17,502 --> 00:47:20,422
You think he ditched the benz
because he picked up the tail?

469
00:47:24,509 --> 00:47:25,760
Mmm.

470
00:47:29,514 --> 00:47:32,475
Nicky, from the docks.

471
00:47:35,937 --> 00:47:38,064
If you hadn't called, I'd
have never found you.

472
00:47:38,148 --> 00:47:40,191
Relax, Niko, come on.

473
00:47:41,484 --> 00:47:43,653
It's like I told you on the phone.

474
00:47:43,737 --> 00:47:46,698
It is going to be all right.
We can make it all right.

475
00:47:46,781 --> 00:47:49,367
I should have never gone
down the road with you.

476
00:47:49,451 --> 00:47:53,705
Come on.
You tried to make something of yourself.

477
00:47:53,788 --> 00:47:55,665
There was no harm in that.

478
00:47:55,749 --> 00:47:58,710
And you still have friends.

479
00:47:58,793 --> 00:48:00,503
I'm busted.

480
00:48:01,463 --> 00:48:06,051
So is my uncle and the whole fucking union.
And Ziggy?

481
00:48:07,302 --> 00:48:09,387
- Christ...
- We will be a friend to him, too.

482
00:48:09,471 --> 00:48:13,475
Nothing you people can do about that.
Ziggy's done.

483
00:48:14,476 --> 00:48:18,063
Nothing is done, Niko. Nothing.

484
00:48:19,856 --> 00:48:20,940
Take a look.

485
00:48:25,987 --> 00:48:27,989
That's not your name.

486
00:48:28,656 --> 00:48:30,825
Many names, many passports.

487
00:48:33,328 --> 00:48:35,163
We could do many things.

488
00:48:40,835 --> 00:48:43,254
What can you do for Ziggy?

489
00:48:47,175 --> 00:48:49,052
We ask only loyalty.

490
00:48:59,854 --> 00:49:01,356
Aaah.

491
00:49:03,108 --> 00:49:06,569
Why do they need sticks?
Can't they kick it with their feet?

492
00:49:08,404 --> 00:49:11,825
She asked me straight up to come in,
so I'm here.

493
00:49:12,367 --> 00:49:15,203
First, we need to know
what you're looking for.

494
00:49:15,286 --> 00:49:18,123
We don't want any misunderstandings
later on.

495
00:49:18,206 --> 00:49:22,544
I'm just looking for, you know,
some help with my son.

496
00:49:23,253 --> 00:49:26,965
- He can'tjail where they got him.
- We move him to a county facility.

497
00:49:28,883 --> 00:49:32,428
- What about my nephew?
- He gets arrested and charged.

498
00:49:32,512 --> 00:49:38,393
But for his cooperation and yours,
we can live with straight probation.

499
00:49:40,728 --> 00:49:43,356
But what we can and cannot do
for you and your family

500
00:49:43,439 --> 00:49:47,569
- depends on the level of your cooperation.
- You mean, how much I give you?

501
00:49:48,945 --> 00:49:50,363
I got dirt on all of 'em.

502
00:49:51,573 --> 00:49:55,201
I'll put myself in, too. Whatever you need.
Anything but the union.

503
00:49:55,285 --> 00:49:59,205
I ain't putting in no union men.
I'll give you them dead girls in the can.

504
00:49:59,289 --> 00:50:01,166
I'll give you the Greek,

505
00:50:01,332 --> 00:50:02,434
just to have it off my chest.

506
00:50:02,458 --> 00:50:04,961
Just look to my son and my nephew.

507
00:50:05,044 --> 00:50:07,338
Mr. Sobotka, at this point,
I have to advise you

508
00:50:07,422 --> 00:50:09,674
you need the services of an attorney.

509
00:50:09,757 --> 00:50:13,386
- We're not gonna do this now?
- You need a lawyer present in the room.

510
00:50:13,469 --> 00:50:16,556
You have that, we can make this happen
first thing tomorrow.

511
00:50:26,149 --> 00:50:30,820
Mr. Sobotka, I gotta ask.
Why did you stop using your cell phone?

512
00:50:31,779 --> 00:50:34,157
You guys flagged it.

513
00:50:34,240 --> 00:50:36,242
You think I didn't know?

514
00:52:00,868 --> 00:52:02,870
Under the bridge, huh?

515
00:52:03,871 --> 00:52:07,625
It's out in the open.
I guess the cops can't bug it or nothing.

516
00:52:07,709 --> 00:52:10,295
These guys,
they got a big operation to protect.

517
00:52:10,378 --> 00:52:11,838
They're global, like.

518
00:52:11,921 --> 00:52:15,300
- They're really something, huh?
- You got no idea.

519
00:52:15,383 --> 00:52:18,636
I think I got a pretty clear picture
of what they're about.

520
00:52:19,721 --> 00:52:23,850
We ain't talking about a bunch of thieves
rolling drums of olive oil off the docks.

521
00:52:23,933 --> 00:52:25,268
Heroin?

522
00:52:25,351 --> 00:52:28,187
How the fuck did that happen, Nick?
Look at me!

523
00:52:29,731 --> 00:52:32,275
You ain't much more than a kid.

524
00:52:34,402 --> 00:52:38,281
Me, I should've known better.
I put you up with them, for what?

525
00:52:40,575 --> 00:52:43,411
I flushed my fucking family, for what?

526
00:52:45,997 --> 00:52:48,541
You know what that is, Nicky? Do you?

527
00:52:51,085 --> 00:52:52,754
A condominium.

528
00:52:58,968 --> 00:53:00,678
I ain't going down there.

529
00:53:00,762 --> 00:53:03,514
What I'm gonna do is
go in and talk with the police.

530
00:53:04,432 --> 00:53:07,185
That's right. I'm gonna do to
those cocksuckers what they did to me.

531
00:53:07,268 --> 00:53:09,729
- You can't do that.
- Why not?

532
00:53:11,773 --> 00:53:13,900
They wanna meet with us on Ziggy.

533
00:53:15,818 --> 00:53:17,528
They can lean on that witness...

534
00:53:17,612 --> 00:53:20,823
That kid that he shot,
the one that was there in the store.

535
00:53:20,907 --> 00:53:23,117
The kid'll say that double g had the gun,

536
00:53:23,201 --> 00:53:25,953
that it was like self-defense or some shit.

537
00:53:27,997 --> 00:53:30,500
Ziggy could walk, uncle frank.

538
00:53:31,000 --> 00:53:32,418
He could.

539
00:53:35,671 --> 00:53:38,257
- And for that they want what?
- Loyalty.

540
00:53:38,341 --> 00:53:40,176
Motherfuckers...

541
00:54:11,999 --> 00:54:14,001
I'll hear 'em out.

542
00:54:15,169 --> 00:54:18,005
- All right, I'll drive.
- No, it's just me.

543
00:54:19,674 --> 00:54:21,384
You ain't dealing with them no more.

544
00:54:21,467 --> 00:54:26,055
- Uncle frank, me and spiros...
- I don't fucking want you with me, Nick!

545
00:54:27,348 --> 00:54:29,142
Go home!

546
00:56:42,191 --> 00:56:43,859
Your way...

547
00:56:45,027 --> 00:56:46,654
It won't work.

